    <p>{`At Kerberos.io we have fast development cycles, which means that new versions will be released every day, week or month. To make sure you can upgrade or downgrade your Kerberos Enterprise agent easily, an upgrade feature is built-in. When pressing the upgrade button, you will be able to select the version to which you would like to upgrade or downgrade. Once submitted, `}<strong parentName="p">{`a zero downtime upgrade will take place`}</strong>{`. Kubernetes will download the new release, create a new pod, and destroy the old one.`}</p>
    <p>{`At any moment you can reboot your Kerberos Enterprise agent. When pressing the reboot button, next to your deployment, Kubernetes will destroy the pod of your deployment, and schedule a new one. This comes in handy, when you noticed one of your Kerberos Enterprise agents is in a stale state.`}</p>
    <p><img alt="Upgrade and reboot" src={require("../../public/images/factory/upgrade-reboot.gif")} /></p>
